18 0 obj
<< /Length 2831 >>
stream
BT
/F1 10 Tf
50 760 Td
12 TL
(PROTOTYPE LADDER) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(P0: FIPPLE HEAD TILE) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Cut a 4 in scrap block with the selected bore diameter or a half-bore test channel.) Tj
T*
(2. Cut the end mouth inlet.) Tj
T*
(3. Fit a removable flue plug with 0.033, 0.038, and 0.045 in shim trials.) Tj
T*
(4. Cut a side true sound window and splitting edge.) Tj
T*
(5. Blow through the end inlet and record which plug/window combination speaks cleanly.) Tj
T*
(6. Do not build a full flute until this tile produces stable tone.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(P1: FIRST KAVAL BODY) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Select KAV-A3-5H.) Tj
T*
(2. Mill the blank overlength by at least 2 in.) Tj
T*
(3. Split the blank, route the bore halves and registration pin holes, or deep-bore the solid) Tj
T*
(blank after proving setup on scrap.) Tj
T*
(4. Create the fipple head and removable plug.) Tj
T*
(5. Prove the root tone with no finger holes.) Tj
T*
(6. Trim the foot to bring the all-closed root toward A3.) Tj
T*
(7. Transfer hole positions from kaval-hole-schedule.csv.) Tj
T*
(8. Drill each hole undersized.) Tj
T*
(9. Tune holes from the foot upward by reaming slowly.) Tj
T*
(10. Record every before/after pitch in validation.csv.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(P1: FIRST ALGHOSAZI BODY) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Select ALG-AS3-J2.) Tj
T*
(2. Build as a solid body first if joint risk feels high; otherwise cut the two-piece joint) Tj
T*
(after the bore is proven.) Tj
T*
(3. Mark the rear thumb-hole line before drilling.) Tj
T*
(4. Drill the thumb hole undersized and validate reach with the actual player grip.) Tj
T*
(5. Tune the primary sequence and record whether the scale feels musically right.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(P2: JOINTED VERSION) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Cut the body overlength and prove tone before final jointing.) Tj
T*
(2. Locate the joint away from holes and away from the fipple head.) Tj
T*
(3. Turn tenon and socket with a 1.25 in engagement target.) Tj
T*
(4. Add cork or waxed thread until the joint seals without force.) Tj
T*
(5. Check bore step with a dowel, light, and feeler test.) Tj
T*
(6. Re-test root and all holes after the joint is fitted.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(P3: DOUBLE DRONE) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Build melody and drone tubes separately.) Tj
T*
(2. Tune the melody side alone.) Tj
T*
(3. Tune the drone side alone, including rear thumb vent if used.) Tj
T*
(4. Join the bodies temporarily with clamps or bands before permanent collars.) Tj
T*
(5. Test pressure sharing with both windways.) Tj
T*
(6. Only then commit to a permanent double-body fixture or decorative binding.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(FINISHING) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Finish exterior after tuning.) Tj
T*
(- Keep heavy oil, shellac, and wax out of the windway and splitting edge.) Tj
T*
(- Seal bore lightly only after final measurements.) Tj
T*
(- Recheck pitch after finish cure.) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
